---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import HeroSection from '../components/HeroSection.astro';
import Promobar from '../components/Promobar.astro';
---

<Layout>
  <Header />
  <main>
    <HeroSection 
      title="Frequently Asked Questions" 
      highlightText="Questions"
      description="Find answers to common questions about our services."
    />
    
    <section class="py-16 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800">
      <div class="container-custom">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
          <!-- FAQ Categories Navigation -->
          
          
          <!-- General FAQs -->
          
          
          <!-- Pricing & Plans FAQs -->
          
          
          <!-- Features FAQs -->
          <div id="features" class="mb-16">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-8 flex items-center">
              <span class="inline-block rounded-full bg-primary-100 dark:bg-blue-900 p-2 mr-3">
                <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-primary-600 dark:text-blue-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5H7a2 2 0 00-2 2v12a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2h-2M9 5a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2M9 5a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2m-3 7h3m-3 4h3m-6-4h.01M9 16h.01"></path>
                </svg>
              </span>
              Features
            </h2>
            
            <div class="space-y-6">
              <div class="card p-6 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Are the websites mobile friendly?</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
                  Absolutely! Our websites are fully responsive and work seamlessly on desktops, tablets, and mobile devices.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="card p-6 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">What are the monthly analytics?</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
                  The monthly analytics is a short summary of the month, which includes an overview of your visitors for that month, pageviews and top pages. Data collection doesn't collect any personal user information and complies with the General Data Protection Regulation. 
                  At the end of each month you will receive an email with your website statistics for that month.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="card p-6 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Do I have to pay for my domain?</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
                  We take care of your domain costs, we will provide you with a domain that displays your business name after an agreement with you. Some domains with popular names are often taken, we aren't responsible for domain availability. 
                  If you wish to cancel your subscription and keep the domain, you should contact us and we will guide you for next steps.
                </p>
              </div>
              
              <div class="card p-6 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">What are considered as minor changes?</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
                  Minor changes are any changes that take less than one hour to implement within the website. Like changing a paragraph or a picture on your website pages. You can submit a change request by email. Your request will then be classified as either minor or major.
                </p><br>
                <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300"><b>Example of minor changes:</b></p>
                <ul class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 list-disc ml-5">
                  <li>Change text in a paragraph</li>
                  <li>Update your website logo</li>
                  <li>Add extra paragraph in an existing section (existing page)</li>
                  <li>Adding colors, fonts to existing elements</li>
                  <li>Replacing existing photos</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              
              <div class="card p-6 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">What are considered as major changes?</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
                  Major changes are any changes that take more than an hour to implement. Adding an extra page to your website would be considered as a major change. You can submit a change request via email which will then be classified.
                </p><br>
                <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300"><b>Example of major changes:</b></p>
                <ul class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 list-disc ml-5">
                  <li>Designing and adding a new page or section</li>
                  <li>Redesigning an existing page layout</li>
                  <li>Implementing custom forms</li>
                  <li>Changing restructuring large amounts of content</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              
              <div class="card p-6 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">What is SEO?</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
                  SEO is short for Search Engine Optimization, it's how people are able to find your business if they search for you online. Search Engine Optimization allows the browser to show the website to people who search for your service near you.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <!-- Support FAQs -->
          <div id="cancellation" class="mb-16">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-8 flex items-center">
              <span class="inline-block rounded-full bg-primary-100 dark:bg-blue-900 p-2 mr-3">
                <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-primary-600 dark:text-blue-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                  <path stroke-width="2" d="M5.47 5.47a.75.75 0 0 1 1.06 0L12 10.94l5.47-5.47a.75.75 0 1 1 1.06 1.06L13.06 12l5.47 5.47a.75.75 0 1 1-1.06 1.06L12 13.06l-5.47 5.47a.75.75 0 0 1-1.06-1.06L10.94 12L5.47 6.53a.75.75 0 0 1 0-1.06Z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
                </svg>
              </span>
              Cancellation
            </h2>
            
            <div class="space-y-6">
              <div class="card p-6 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">How do I cancel this service?</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
                  You can contact us before the start of your next billing cycle so we can cancel your subscription. Email <b>snapsites4u@gmail.com</b> with your request. To ensure you don't get accidentally charged for the next period, it's best to cancel a couple days before your next monthly charge.
                </p>
              </div>
              
              <div class="card p-6 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Do you offer refunds?</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
                  No, we do not offer refunds. If you cancel after you paid for your next month, we will host your website and provide support for that month, and your cancellation will take effect next month.
                </p>
              </div>
              
              <div class="card p-6 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">What happens after I cancel?</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
                  After you cancel, we will continue hosting and support until the month you paid for expires, so if you cancel 15 days into your subscription, we will continue support and hosting for another 15 days (in a 30 day month). After the 15 days we will stop hosting your website and it will be unaccessible. 
                  Once you cancel, you won't be charged anymore, unless you restart your subscription. If you wish to claim your domain after cancellation, you can contact us and we will guide you with next steps.
                </p>
              </div>
              
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="text-center mt-16">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">Still have questions?</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">
              Our team is here to help. Contact us and we'll get back to you as soon as possible.
            </p>
            <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">Contact Support</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>

